#: ../../../basic/pgtypes.rst:11
msgid "Adapting other PostgreSQL types"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../basic/pgtypes.rst:13
msgid ""
"PostgreSQL offers other data types which don't map to native Python types. "
"Psycopg offers wrappers and conversion functions to allow their use."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../basic/pgtypes.rst:25
msgid "Composite types adaptation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../basic/pgtypes.rst:27
msgid ""
"Psycopg can adapt PostgreSQL composite types (either created with the |"
"CREATE TYPE|_ command or implicitly defined after a table row type) to and "
"from Python tuples, `~collections.namedtuple`, or any suitably configured "
"object."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../basic/pgtypes.rst:34
msgid ""
"Before using a composite type it is necessary to get information about it "
"using the `~psycopg.types.composite.CompositeInfo` class and to register it "
"using `~psycopg.types.composite.register_composite()`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.14/site-packages/psycopg/types/composite.py:docstring
#: of psycopg.types.composite.CompositeInfo:1
msgid "Manage information about a composite type."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../basic/pgtypes.rst:40
msgid ""
"`!CompositeInfo` is a `~psycopg.types.TypeInfo` subclass: check its "
"documentation for the general usage, especially the `~psycopg.types.TypeInfo."
"fetch()` method."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../basic/pgtypes.rst:47
msgid "Tuple containing the field names of the composite type."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../basic/pgtypes.rst:52
msgid "Tuple containing the field OIDs of the composite type."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../basic/pgtypes.rst:57
msgid ""
"After `register_composite()` is called, it will contain the Python type "
"adapting the registered composite."
msgstr ""

